Then, square the result:
\[
(16.030792)^2 = 256.986292
\]

The sample size $n$ must be an integer. Since $n$ must be at least 256.986 to ensure the margin of error is no larger than 0.25, round up to the nearest integer. Thus, $n = 257$.

The preliminary sample size of 32 is used only to provide $s$, and the calculated $n=257$ is larger, so no further iteration is necessary. The sample size required is 257.

