- \(P(P \text{ and } C) = 0.28\)
- \(P(\text{neither}) = 0.08\)
- \(P(P) = P(C) + 0.16\)

First, \(P(P \text{ or } C) = 1 - P(\text{neither}) = 1 - 0.08 = 0.92\).

Using the formula for the union:
\[
P(P \text{ or } C) = P(P) + P(C) - P(P \text{ and } C)
\]
Substitute the known values:
\[
0.92 = (P(C) + 0.16) + P(C) - 0.28
\]
Simplify:
\[
0.92 = 2P(C) + 0.16 - 0.28
\]
\[
0.92 = 2P(C) - 0.12
\]
Solve for \(P(C)\):
\[
0.92 + 0.12 = 2P(C)
\]
\[
1.04 = 2P(C)
\]
\[
P(C) = 0.52
\]
Then:
\[
P(P) = P(C) + 0.16 = 0.52 + 0.16 = 0.68
\]

Verification:
- \(P(P \text{ or } C) = 0.68 + 0.52 - 0.28 = 0.92\)
- \(P(\text{neither}) = 1 - 0.92 = 0.08\), which matches.
- The difference \(P(P) - P(C) = 0.68 - 0.52 = 0.16\), which matches the 16% excess.

The probability of visiting a physical therapist is 0.68.

