(a) Find the probability that the length of life of the bulb from company $A$ exceeds the length of life of the bulb from company $B$ by at least 15 hours.
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The random variable \(X\) represents the life length of a bulb from company A, distributed as \(N(800, 14400)\), and \(Y\) represents the life length of a bulb from company B, distributed as \(N(850, 2500)\). The bulbs are independent since one is randomly selected from each company.

The goal is to find \(P(X - Y \geq 15)\).

