Solution: The problem involves finding the probability of no matches (derangement) when selecting n balls without replacement, where a match occurs if ball m is selected on the m-th draw. The probability of no matches is given by the number of derangements divided by the total number of permutations, which is \( \frac{D(n)}{n!} = \sum_{k=0}^{n} \frac{(-1)^k}{k!} \).

